</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="81B6651AFFE2FFE44DD1FEC9FB0D91E5" pageId="5" pageNumber="585" type="description">
<paragraph id="C9133691FFE2FFE44DD1FEC9FE40927D" blockId="5.[151,1437,258,931]" box="[151,403,258,283]" pageId="5" pageNumber="585">
Length. Male: 
<quantity id="0E549B74FFE2FFE44C7BFEC9FE5D927D" box="[317,398,258,283]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="585" unit="mm" value="6.2">6.2mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C9133691FFE2FFE44D81FEEDFA4B92CD" blockId="5.[151,1437,258,931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis id="FBD8EA83FFE2FFE44D81FEEDFDE29259" bold="true" box="[199,561,294,319]" pageId="5" pageNumber="585">Colouration and Morphology:</emphasis>
Shiny pale yellow in appearance (Plate IH). Crown with two transverse lines on anterior margin. Pronotum pale yellow, scutellum with fuscous yellowish spots. Forewings yellowish with pale veins (Plate IH–I). Crown subangularly produced and broadly triangular with dorsal marginal ridge. Ocelli on margin next to eyes. Genae strongly sinuate below eyes. Pronotum as wide as head, laterally carinate (Plate IH–J).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C9133691FFE2FFE44D81FE7DFB0D91E5" blockId="5.[151,1437,258,931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis id="FBD8EA83FFE2FFE44D81FE7DFEE692A9" bold="true" box="[199,309,438,463]" pageId="5" pageNumber="585">Genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygofer lobe subacute apically, heavily setose in posterior half (
<figureCitation id="51972A14FFE2FFE44950FE7DFBA292A9" box="[1046,1137,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1959,1981]" captionTargetBox="[178,1418,1039,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,1031,1893]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hecalus muzaffarabadensis sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, connective, valve and subgenital Plate, dorsal view; C. aedeagus, dorsal view; D. aedeagus lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242044/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="585">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Valve broadly triangular. Connective “Y”-shaped with short stem. Subgenital plates elongate, broader at base, tapered apically with 6–7 submarginal setae. Style with pointed apophysis, with scales, preapical lobe moderately developed (
<figureCitation id="51972A14FFE2FFE44874FE35FA5D9171" box="[1330,1422,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1959,1981]" captionTargetBox="[178,1418,1039,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,1031,1893]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hecalus muzaffarabadensis sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, connective, valve and subgenital Plate, dorsal view; C. aedeagus, dorsal view; D. aedeagus lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242044/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="585">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with dorsal apodeme finger-like, curved distad (
<figureCitation id="51972A14FFE2FFE44E73FDE9FC42915D" box="[821,913,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1959,1981]" captionTargetBox="[178,1418,1039,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,1031,1893]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hecalus muzaffarabadensis sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, connective, valve and subgenital Plate, dorsal view; C. aedeagus, dorsal view; D. aedeagus lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242044/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="585">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft broadened medially; tapered distally with terminal pair of forked processes, ventral fork longer (
<figureCitation id="51972A14FFE2FFE44EE7FD8DFC2F9139" box="[929,1020,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1959,1981]" captionTargetBox="[178,1418,1039,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,1031,1893]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hecalus muzaffarabadensis sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, connective, valve and subgenital Plate, dorsal view; C. aedeagus, dorsal view; D. aedeagus lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242044/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="585">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft with pair of lateral flares around constriction near apex; keeled ventrally with many teeth (
<figureCitation id="51972A14FFE2FFE44EF3FDA1FBDE91E5" box="[949,1037,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1959,1981]" captionTargetBox="[178,1418,1039,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,1031,1893]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hecalus muzaffarabadensis sp. nov. A. PygoPhore, lateral view; B. style, connective, valve and subgenital Plate, dorsal view; C. aedeagus, dorsal view; D. aedeagus lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242044/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="585">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
